&lt;h2 id="1-install-firmware">1. Install firmware&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Download &lt;a href="https://downloads.circuitpython.org/bin/raspberry_pi_pico/en_US/adafruit-circuitpython-raspberry_pi_pico-en_US-8.0.5.uf2">firmware file&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Plug in your Pico (showing as a USB drive called RPI-RP2_)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Copy the firmware file you downloaded onto the Pico&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The Pico will sutomatically disconnect and reappear as a USB drive called CIRCUITPY.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h2 id="2-open-file-and-test-code">2. Open file and test code&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol start="5">
&lt;li>Open Mu Editor.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Choose &lt;code>Load&lt;/code>, and find the CIRCUITPY drive. Open the file called code.py. This is the program file the Pico is executing.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Copy in the [starter code] from the website.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Check that the built-in green light next to the USB port flashes. Change the sleep timings to adjust the flash pattern.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h2 id="3-solder-components">3. Solder components&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol start="9">
&lt;li>Watch the &lt;a href="https://tmccatholiceduau-my.sharepoint.com/:v:/g/personal/aknight_tmc_catholic_edu_au/ESbtkG_fkwNArYszbg9YyEsBX8ulkV_4hPzuVSXzYMH4_w?e=ES3aD6">soldering tutorial&lt;/a>.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol></description></item></channel></rss>